name: MistralAIModel

input.content: What port has 5 pins on the top and 4 on the bottom?

output: The description you provided seems to refer to a VGA (Video Graphics Array) port. This port is typically used to connect a computer to a monitor. It has 15 pins in total, arranged in three rows of five. However, if you're looking at the port with the opening facing up, it would appear as two rows on top (5 pins each) and one row at the bottom (4 pins, with one pin missing in the middle).
